main event: On 30 March 1966, a witness observed an unidentified object in Kettering, Ohio, which appeared to be moving rapidly across the sky.
interesting points: The object was reported to be as bright as a star and fading,The object was observed for a total of 10-15 minutes,It moved in a zig-zag motion,The object was identified in the report as a satellite (PEGASUS II),No photographic evidence was present in the report.
sighted object: one bright object moving in the sky
witness description: The witness stated they were outdoors and observed the object under bright daylight conditions.
